The Telegraph - Calcutta : Sports

 Shoaib has to prove fitness

Karachi: A PCB official made it clear on Saturday that Shoaib Akhtar would be allowed to take part in next months Afro-Asia Cup only if he proves his fitness. 

Shoaib, after initial reluctance to play in the meet citing personal commitments and lack of match fitness, subsequently made himself available for the three matches to be held in Bangalore and Chennai. 

Mohammed Yousuf and Mohammed Asif are the other Pakistan players in the Asia XI squad. 

